==============================================================
  EXAMPLE — GitHub Release Provider
  THIS FILE IS AN EXAMPLE ONLY. It will do nothing here in
  the repo root. To use it:
  1. Copy this file into the mod folder you want to auto-update.
  2. Rename it to exactly  update.json  (remove "GitHubReleaseExample-").
  3. Edit the values below ==== to match the mod's GitHub repository.

  NOTE: update.json is automatically preserved across updates —
  the updater backs it up and restores it, so you will not lose
  your config when the mod itself gets updated.

  FIELD REFERENCE:
  - "provider"               Must be "github". (Required)
  - "repo"                   GitHub owner/repo, e.g. "AuthorName/CoolBalatroMod". (Required)
  - "asset_regex"            Regex to match the correct .zip asset in the release.
                             Defaults to ".*\.zip$" if omitted. Useful when a release
                             has multiple assets and you need to pick the right one. (Optional)
  - "strip_single_top_folder" If true (default), and the zip contains exactly one
                             top-level folder, its contents are extracted directly into
                             the mod folder instead of creating a nested sub-folder.
                             Set to false to disable this behaviour. (Optional)
==============================================================

{
    "provider":                 "github",
    "repo":                     "AuthorName/CoolBalatroMod",
    "asset_regex":              ".*\\.zip$",
    "strip_single_top_folder":  true
}
